<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">Posts from Gordon Wrinn on the offical EQ board</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=146036" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047429.html">Everlore? (Abashi please reply)</a><P>

I was wondering if Anyone from Verant reads/looks at the polls taken on Everlore?<P>

<B>Sure, from time to time. I try to keep an eye on what's going on from site to site.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/046134.html">Resist Rates on Necro Darkness Series - why?</a><P>

I hope Verant reads this posts and responds. I'd like to know why the resist rate on the darkness series of spells is so high.<P>

<B>The resist rates for the spell is the same as other magic-based spells such as fear, or root. Targets to not get dual saving throws for the spell. It certainly lands more than half the time on low greens assuming that the target isn't immune to magic.<P>

Personally, I didn't use the spell regularly until the high 30s due to the resists and mana costs. After that it became quite reliable and economical, and I rarely get a resist on a non-immune blue.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047231.html">Gordon, why are you sidestepping the real issue on RZ?</a><P>

You've answered a few posts recently that have related to RZ but have yet to respond to the main issue.<P>

In case you aren't sure just what it is, I'll restate it for you:<P>

We want the ebay boys to go away.<P>

<B>As I've said in previous posts, the only thing that we have planned currently is allowing people to move between TZ and VZ to determine what loot rules people as a whole generally prefer. Any further plans in regards to server rulesets will need to wait until this happens.<P>

As for RZ going coin-only, that too will need to wait until we have more data. I've received a ton of emails both ways on the subject, and am aware of the concerns of both sides. I do hope that there is a solution to be found that will please both groups, but as mentioned above, any further plans will be on hold pending the results of the current one. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047328.html">Does Verant Actually Believe that Everyone Can Get a Resurrect Everytime They Die?</a><P>

It just seems that the exp penalty post 50 is set like you will get a 49 exp res everytime you die.<P>

<B>Everyone, everytime? Of course not. Enough of the time to mitigate some of the experience loss to the point that it encourages people to make friends with classes that can rez? Sure.<P>

As with many other issues, EverQuest players are responsible for determining the level of risk that is acceptable to them. If the risk of dying without a rez is too great to be palatable, then players need to take steps to mitigate that risk. They can do this by adventuring with cleris, paladins, and the occasional necro who might be conned out of an essense emerald, or by adventuring into situations only where the death potential is managable.<P> 

I know that I've said the same thing as above for many different issues lately, but it seems that a lot of the complaints lately are on issues where the amount of risk encountered is primarily controlled by the player. <P>

Players are in control of their destiny and the amount of risk that they are willing to absorb. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047330.html">Patch during 3-6am not daylight hours!</a><P>

Any major telco/ISP i've worked with does their maint work during low usage hours, ie: 3-6am local time when the majority of their customers aren't using their service. pay someone the OT 3rd shift money to come in and do your patches then<P>

<B>3-6am is still pretty busy on the servers. In any case, 3rd shift money hasn't anything to do with our selection of downtimes. It's a combination of the inevitability of affecting people when taking a game down that is played internationally, meaning that it's always someone's primetime play time, and the fact that we like to be sure that we have the entire EverQuest team at arms length when making a patch in case anything unforeseen happens.<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047402.html">Gordon ...kudos to you and the rest of the EQ team</a><P>

Here it is. After a full year of playing EQ and thoroughly enjoying it I have to give a standing ovation to the every person involved in its development and support.<P>

<B>Thanks guys! It's great to see positive posts here from time to time. I'm glad to hear that you are having a good time.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047450.html">Blood Ember Vambraces weight is double Deepwater Vambraces weight</a><P>

Blood Ember Vambraces (13.0 weight) are double the weight of most of the other pieces of Blood Ember armor (6.5 weight is the mode on the pieces that have been found so far).<P>

<B>After a second look we've decided to lower the weight on the breastplate and helm. It will go live in the next item patch.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047460.html">Abashi- Nerf the Ring of the Ancients!</a><P>

Alright, I read the post saying you're happy with the drop rate of the Ring of the Ancients. But please make it have no stats or only +3int so that high level casters WITH jboots already dont ks people trying to get boots for themselves merely for the sake of picking up +2int over a Polished Bone Bracer. This is a REAL problem..I've seen many high level casters with jboots KS lower level groups trying to get the Ring in order to do the quest. IMO thats very selfish of them to deprive people the opportunity to get jboots and poor decision making by Verant in regard to the Ring's stats caused the problem.<P>

<B>Considering how easy it is to reach 200+ int, I'm surprised that people would KS a rare spawn to get an item that is a mere +1 INT better than something else easily obtainable by them. In any case, as I mentioned in a thread yesterday, we're pleased with the rate that JBoots are coming into the game at the moment. If the fact that casters want to wear this ring is partly responsible for the speed that jboots are coming in game, we probably wouldn't want to change it.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047466.html">Somethings just annoy...</a><P>

What is the point of having two slots for bracers, but not sleeves?<P>

<B>Basically, it's just the way it was designed, and besides, two different sleeves would look funny :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047470.html">Wiz Flamin Sword. Interesting Idea. ABASHI can you confirm/deny this idea??????????</a><P>

He says that this IS NOT A PET.. DONT treat it like one... GREAT!!! I never Ever wanted a stupid pet.... So this is a spell which you can cast during battle to do 'great amounts' of damage (to me 50hp off a mob that you are fighting at that level is like sticking them with a stick, but whatever)..<P>

<B>Well, though not precisely a pet from a gameplay standpoint per se, it is a pet from a game engine standpoint, so having more than one at a time would be prohibited. <P>

I'd think of the spell more like a DOT spell than a pet.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047471.html">Abashi i know your lurking</a><P>

So PLEASE answer my question regarding the (non) no drop status of the cleric and shaman belts in POF. They should be NO DROP. The druid belt is no drop but the cleric belt and shaman belts arent.<P>

<B>Considering the numbers of new items from Kunark that are neither nodrop or lore, we probably won't be applying those tags to anything that has been missing them in game all of this time. <P>

For those on the PvP servers where loot is still a possibility, it's basically another case where you decide what risk is good for you and play the game to that end. If the possibility of losing an item in PvP combat is too great, it is you choice as to whether or not you want to wear it in a situation where PvP is possible.<P>

Cases like this where players make a decision about the level of risk that they are willing to accept are quite common in game.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047475.html">Possible bug related to Tashania recast delay</a><P>

Since the last patch, I've noticed that if I cast Tashania as soon as it becomes available, either due to casting another spell and waiting for the spell icons to reset or casting tashania and waiting for its icon to reset, it will go through a full casting time then display a message that states something along the lines of 'The recast delay of this spell was not met'.<P>

<B>Interesting problem. I'll bring it to the attention of GZ and the client programmer. Thanks for letting us know.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047481.html">Recent news: Layoffs at SONY. What does this mean for Everquest?</a><P>

What does this mean for Everquest? Does it end?<P>

<B>There are more than a few inaccuracies in the article, of which I really can't comment on specifics at this time. However, just so everyone is aware, EverQuest operations and development will not be adversely affected by any of what is going on. <P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/047488.html">Dmg Shield up, yet still interrupted. More details inside.. Any help would be Great!</a><P>

I have noticed lately that when I am soloing in Kunark, I find that with my damage shield casted on myself, (leatherskin, level 24 Wiz spell, havent checked out shield skin the level 20 spell) that Mobs can still interrupt my casting...<P>

<B>Damage shields still allow interruptions to take place. <P>

Back in beta, they used to shield you from all damage and interruptions. I recall that I was able to take a wizard, load on diamondskin, and conflag an ice giant to death before it could get through the diamondskin.<P> 

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
